        <dc:title>Migration, family context, and child health</dc:title>
        <dcterms:abstract>As international labor migration becomes a more common livelihood strategy globally, this widespread population and social change has profound demographic and health consequences, including for young children left behind by migrating parents or family members. Many children left behind receive remittance income from migrant parents or family members. However, identifying the effects of this additional […]</dcterms:abstract>
